[al:新概念英语（三）]
[ar:MP3 同步字幕版（美音）]
[ti:Five Pounds Too Dear]
[00:00.36]Lesson 28|第28课
[00:02.68]Five pounds too dear|价格贵了五英镑……
[00:10.72]Why was even five pounds 'too dear' ?|为什么哪怕只有五磅的重量也被认为“太贵”了呢？
[00:16.88]Small boats loaded with wares sped to the great liner as she was entering the harbour.|当那艘大型客轮驶入港口时，载满货物的小船迅速朝它驶去。
[00:23.63]Before she had anchored, the men from the boats had climbed on board|在她抛下锚之前，那些来自小船上的男人就已经爬上了船。
[00:28.49]and the decks were soon covered with colourful rugs from Persia,|很快，这些甲板上就铺上了来自波斯的彩色地毯。
[00:33.30]silks from India, copper coffee pots, and beautiful handmade silverware.|来自印度的丝绸、铜制的咖啡壶，以及精美的手工银器。
[00:40.08]It was difficult not to be tempted.|很难抗拒这种诱惑。
[00:43.30]Many of the tourists on board had begun bargaining with the tradesmen,|船上的许多游客已经开始与商贩们讨价还价了。
[00:47.47]but I decided not to buy anything until I had disembarked.|但我决定在下车之前不购买任何东西。
[00:53.56]I had no sooner got off the ship than I was assailed by a man who wanted to sell me a diamond ring.|我刚下船，就立刻被一个男人缠住了——他想要向我推销一枚钻石戒指。
[01:02.16]I had no intention of buying one,|我本来就没有打算买一个的。
[01:04.87]but I could not conceal the fact that I was impressed by the size of the diamonds.|但我无法隐瞒这样一个事实：这些钻石的尺寸确实让我印象深刻。
[01:11.44]Some of them were as big as marbles.|其中一些球的大小和弹珠差不多。
[01:14.63]The man went to great lengths to prove that the diamonds were real.|这个人付出了巨大的努力来证明这些钻石是真品。
[01:19.90]As we were walking past a shop, he held a diamond firmly against the window and made a deep impression in the glass.|当我们经过一家商店时，他用力将那颗钻石压在窗户上，从而在玻璃上留下了一个明显的印记。
[01:28.90]It took me over half an hour to get rid of him.|我花了半个多小时才把他弄走。
[01:32.93]The next man to approach me was selling expensive pens and watches.|下一个向我走来的人在推销昂贵的钢笔和手表。
[01:38.10]I examined one of the pens closely. It certainly looked genuine.|我仔细检查了其中一支笔，它看起来确实很 genuine（即非常逼真、质量上乘）。
[01:43.79]At the base of the gold cap, the words 'made in the U.S.A.' had been neatly inscribed.|在金质奖杯的底部，刻着“Made in the U.S.A.”（美国制造）这几个字，字迹非常工整。
[01:52.31]The man said that the pen was worth ￡50, but as a special favour, he would let me have it for ￡30.|那个人说这支笔的价值是 50 英镑，但作为一项特别的优惠，他愿意以 30 英镑的价格把笔卖给我。
[02:02.21]I shook my head and held up five fingers indicating that I was willing to pay ￡5.|我摇了摇头，然后竖起了五根手指，表示我愿意支付 5 英镑。
[02:10.51]Gesticulating wildly, the man acted as if he found my offer outrageous,|那个男人疯狂地比划着手势，表现得好像我的提议让他感到非常愤怒（或难以接受）。
[02:17.42]but he eventually reduced the price to 10 pounds.|但他最终将价格降到了10英镑。
[02:22.62]Shrugging my shoulders I began to walk away when,|我耸了耸肩，正准备走开时，突然……
[02:26.62]a moment later, he ran after me and thrust the pen into my hands.|过了一会儿，他追上来，把那支笔塞到了我的手里。
[02:33.35]Though he kept throwing up his arms in despair, he readily accepted the ￡5 I gave him.|尽管他不断绝望地举起双手表示抗拒，但他还是欣然接受了我给他的那5英镑。
[02:40.57]I felt especially pleased with my wonderful bargain--until I got back to the ship.|我对这笔“超值”的交易感到非常满意——直到我回到船上。
[02:47.77]No matter how hard I tried,|无论我多么努力，
[02:50.58]it was impossible to fill this beautiful pen with ink and to this day it has never written a single word!|这枝漂亮的钢笔根本无法装上墨水；直到今天，它仍然一个字也没写过！
